notes:
Making his 122nd career PGA TOUR start, Sean O'Hair posted a 3-under 69 to finish the Quail Hollow Championship at 11-under 277, one stroke ahead of Bubba Watson (70)and Lucas Glover (71). It was the third victory of O'Hair's career(2005 John Deere Classic, 2008 PODS Championship).  
  
 In seven years of the Quail Hollow Championship, the third-round leader has gone on to victory three times( David Toms -2003;   Jim Furyk -2006; and Anthony Kim -2008). Prior to the 2009 final round( Zach Johnson -T13), the third-round leader/co-leader at this event had not finished worse than T3( Rory Sabbatini -2007).
